narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments:
I gained a wealth of knowledge throughout this course. Each week, I actively engaged in absorbing new insights about East Asian women, delving into their lives and exploring their remarkable artwork. The class sessions were thoughtfully structured, featuring extensive reading lists that not only comprehensively covered the subject matter but also included relevant materials.

Visiting the museum to view the artwork proved to be an enlightening and invaluable experience, allowing me to appreciate the pieces in person and deepen my understanding of the artistic context. The course broadened my perspective by introducing me to the often-overlooked art history of women in China, Japan, and Korea. As someone of East Asian descent, I was genuinely surprised to discover many artists and works that I had not encountered or heard of before.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course was very advanced and organized well. The reading lists are challenging and very interesting.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! Professor Wargula is so knowledgeable and kind. She gives you lots of freedom to explore the topics that interest you the most and chooses really cool stuff for us to see from the YUAGs collection.
Absolutely yes! Prof Wargula is such an amazing, knowledgeable teacher.

I highly recommend this course to students studying art or art history.
Although I was getting introduced to new work and time period/country each week, I was getting into the emotional and intellectual depth of the subject. Readings not only expanded my knowledge but also exposed me to a diverse art history and subjects.
